dialogue.string: 1�Welcome, adventurer.This is Rabao, a precious oasis in the middle of the vast Altepa Desert.Take the chance to revitalize yourself before continuing on your journey.
1�Hail, fellow adventurer.My name is Maryoh-Comyujah.I braved the long, arrrduous journey from the mainland to search for trrreasure in the Quicksand Caves.
1�It's been a little harrrder than I expected, though.The Quicksand Caves are extensive and verrry confusing.
1�On top of that, there are all these ant-type beastmen crawling around down there. Not a nice place to be looking for lost rrriches!
1�The rrroad to hidden trrreasure is long indeed...
1�What's up? You changed your mind?
1�Ho there! Aren't you the adventurer known as  ?The winds carry word of your interest in the ruins of Li'Telor.
1�I know how to get in. Into the very center of the rrruins, I mean. I wouldn't mind just telling you, but...you know what they say, ??Nothing of value should come for free.??
1�I have a little favor to ask.Underneath the Altepa Desert lie the expansive Quicksand Caves. I've got a hunch that there's some undiscovered trrreasure in there, still waiting to be claimed.
1�Just head a short way into the caves and pick up anything that strrrikes you as valuable. If I like what you brrring me, I'll tell you everything I know about the rrruins.
1�Not a bad deal, rrright?You scrrratch my back, and I'll scrrratch yours.
1�Do a deal with Maryoh Comyujah?Sounds fair.I can scratch my own back.
1�What, you don't trrrust me?Well, I'll be arrround here for a while, so come on back if you change your mind.
1�Okay then, it's a deal.The Quicksand Caves are expansive and have many entrances, but I'm sure you'll figure them out.
1�My hunter's instinct tells me that there's something unusual beyond that weight-operated device in the caves.
1�Wow, this is incrrredible!
1�Now listen carefully, and I'll tell you what I know about the rrruins, just like I prrromised.
1�What I'm about to tell you happened long before I came to Kuzotz.I went alone to explore Li'Telor, a place that has been known as a holy land since ancient times.
1�I was traveling through a dense fog and, though it embarrasses me to rrrecall, completely lost my way. After wandering for a time, I somehow found myself at the rrruins.
1�What I saw there, you already know.Those huge statues facing one another in that great hall, and beyond...The immovable wall that bars the way into the heart of the rrruins.
1�I searched every inch of that place.And then I found it. A mysterrrious crystal glowing with a clear, blue light.
1�I don't know why it was there, but it was shining from below the surface of the lake in the great hall....Glowing as if in rrresponse to the moonlight that poured in from above.
1�This is that 3????.I brought it back with me thinking I could sell it, but I haven't been able to find a buyer.I might as well give it to you.
1�Place it into the hollow in the center of that wall and see what happens for yourself. You wouldn't want me to spoil it for you now, would you? Hehehe.
1�Those rrruins in Li'Telor are interesting to visit on a night of the full moon.You learn anew that there are still many things in this world that are beyond our understanding.
1�Ho,  .What did you see? There's nothing in there, rrright?I already knew that, though... Huh? You saw a floating island in there?
1�Haha, nice try. If you're gonna make something up, try for something a little more believable. There's nothing at the top of those stairs besides that altar.
1�You see those windmills spinning atop the towers?They use the power of the wind to draw water up from deep beneath the earth.
1�Even during the dry months, Rabao never lacks for water. Getting the water up to the surface originally must have been quite a feat, though.
1�You should show your gratitude to the pioneers of this place.Why, my heart's about to burst from all the gratitude I'm feeling.Thank you, thank you, thank you...!
1�After going through all the trouble of drawing up the water for the oasis, the pioneers of this place stocked it with fish. You can't argue with that kind of thoroughness, hehehe.
1�The Antica beastmen that make their homes here are covered in rigid plates. It's like they're born with a natural suit of armor.
1�You won't be able to make a dent on them without a decent weapon.So saying, I still have to get a new sword, myself. Being a warrior can be so expensive...
1�Behold! The sign upon this arch proclaims the existence of the auction house beyond. A bounty of food and supplies in the center of the desert! What more could one ask for in this life?
1�Oh, you again.I won't bore ya with a long speech. If ya feel up to getting us some #????, I'll be standing right here.
1�The desert is crossed by all sorts of people, not just you adventurers. Like us caravan merchants, for instance.
1�Sometimes we gotta dump our goods and run like hell when we get attacked by monsters out there. Your life is the most valuable thing ya got, pal.
1�Some of the more nasty critters out there are those huge scorpions. They gotta be more'n twice my height, and naturally the sting in the tail'll shoot ya full of poison.

1�Those scorpions are a real pain in the backside, if ya get my meaning. It's fine if ya happen to be best friends with a white mage, but out here you'll find more bruisers than healers. If ya don't got a good stock of antidotes, you're a dead man.
1�'Course, the main ingredient for that antidote just happens to be  $????.
1�An adventurer like yourself should see where I'm going with this. I want ya to go out and get me  $????.
1�Are ya up for it?Leave it to me.Are ya crazy?
1�Oh, I really thought ya would've helped us out...Well, sorry for taking up ya time.
1�Thanks, pal, you're a lifesaver!Now get out there, whack some of them scorpions, and bring me  $????. I'll have ya reward waiting for ya.
1�Got me  $???? yet? I took ya to be a competent adventurer, but don't go getting yourself killed out there.
1�Ya got me another #????!Can't have enough of this stuff. Take this for ya troubles.
1�Ya got the #????!Now I can make me some antidote. Thanks, pal. Here's your reward, like I promised.
1�If ya come across any more of the stuff, bring it to me, and I'll buy it off ya.
1�Oh, you again.If ya come across any more %????, bring 'em to me and I'll buy 'em off ya.
1�The desert is crossed by all sorts of people, not just you adventurers. Like us caravan merchants, for instance.
1�Sometimes we gotta dump our goods and run like hell when we get attacked by monsters out there. Your life is the most valuable thing ya got, pal.
1�There's a cave system at the north edge of the Western Altepa Desert called the Kuftal Tunnel. Cape Teriggan lies at the other end of those caves.
1�A few decades ago, you could easily travel from the cape further into the Quon continent. However, that path was lost when the land itself shifted during the Great War.
1�I am Alfesar, a friar from the San d'Oria Cathedral. I have come to study the Altepa Desert and its surroundings.
1�Until only recently, the monster-infested Korroloka Tunnel has been a barrier between the Quon continent and Zepwell Island. But with the clearing of that tunnel, I was able to make my way here.
1�On your way here to Rabao, I'm sure you saw the ruins of ages past half-buried in the sand. I have been given the task of investigating those ruins.
1�Several days ago, a researcher I hired brought back 6???? inscribed with ancient writings. He found it in the expansive Quicksand Caves that lie beneath the Altepa Desert.
1�This was a major discovery. According to a scholar of ancient literature, the inscription on the tablet appears to be some kind of spell.
1�Unfortunately, with an important part of the tablet broken away, we were unable to decipher the full meaning.
1�I am still undergoing training and do not possess the ability to survive a foray into a place like the Quicksand Caves. And so, I turn to you.
1� , you are highly regarded as an accomplished adventurer. I wish to employ you to venture into the Quicksand Caves and find the remaining 3????.
1�I humbly beg this favor of you.
1�The tablet I have was found in the Quicksand Caves that lie beneath the Altepa Desert. The 3???? will most likely be among other rubble and debris.
1�I humbly beg this favor of you.
1�Yes...This is, without a doubt, the 3????.
1�Please take the completed 3???? and this letter of introduction.
1�With these in your possession, go and meet with Charlaimagnat on the lower level of the San d'Oria Cathedral.
1�Please hand this letter of introduction and the 3???? to Charlaimagnat. He can be found on the lower level of the San d'Oria Cathedral.
1�Ah,  .I received a letter from Charlaimagnat informing me of the safe arrival of the 3????. I am most grateful for your assistance.
1�You have performed a great service for us. , may Paradise open its gates to you.
1�I am Alfesar, a friar from the San d'Oria Cathedral. I have come to study the Altepa Desert and its surroundings.
1�A little further north of here is the Rabao oasis. It's not much, but there are goods for sale in the tents.

1�Outside of Rabao, the desert stretches for as far as the eye can see. Rabao is the only place to gather supplies for your journey and acts as a waypoint for adventurers. It's important for us to work together out here.
1�You probably weren't aware of it, but this island is the lost homeland of the Galka...Even in these endless sands, the joy of setting foot in your homeland is a difficult emotion to express.
1�From ages past, Zepwell Island has been treated as a forbidden land. The passages here from the mainland, the Gustav and Korroloka tunnels, have been inaccessible.
1�But adventurers rarely heed words like ??forbidden,?? now do they? You seem like one of those types.
1�A group of like-minded people, avoiding the authorities from their countries, made their way to this island. They set up shop here, using this oasis as a base.
1�This is Rabao, a town founded by adventurers.
1�Hey, did you know?The ruins that are buried beneath the desert in the Quicksand Caves were once a splendor-wendorous construction of the Galka.
1�Long before either you or I were born, in an age when the Antica and the Galka waged war for dominance over the region, those buildings used to stand on the surface of the desert.
1�And now they crumble below the shifting sands...Even as a Tarutaru, it gets me down. The home of an entire race, disappearing from the light of the sun...
1�I'm a traveling moogle, kupo. I help adventurers in the Outlands access items they have stored in a Mog House elsewhere, kupo.
1�This isn't a Mog House, so you can only use the ??Mog Safe,?? ??Change Jobs,?? and ??Delivery Box?? commands, kupo.

1�You have to pay fee of 
� gil to transfer your items to the Outlands, kupo. Why? Because the world is a cold place for rogue moogles, kupo.

1�Of course, you can move your items back to your Mog House in town, but if you want to transfer them to the Outlands again, you'll have to pay another fee, kupo. I've got to make a living too, kupo.
